President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday sworn in four newly-appointed permanent secretaries during the federal executive council (FEC) meeting in Aso Rock Villa, Abuja. The permanent secretaries are Mary Ada Ogbe, Shehu Ibrahim, Kachollom Shangti Daju, and Beatrice Ejodamen Jedy-Agba. See pictures below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-691750" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-swears-in-appointed-permanent-secretaries.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-swears-in-appointed-permanent-secretaries.jpg 600w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-swears-in-appointed-permanent-secretaries-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-swears-in-appointed-permanent-secretaries-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-swears-in-appointed-permanent-secretaries-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-swears-in-appointed-permanent-secretaries-48x32.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-691751" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/FEC-Meeting.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/FEC-Meeting.jpg 600w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/FEC-Meeting-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/FEC-Meeting-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/FEC-Meeting-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/FEC-Meeting-48x32.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-691752" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/FEC-Meeting-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400"